  "original_title": "\u0db7\u0dcf\u0dab\u0dca\u0da9 \u0dbd\u0dd0\u0dba\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dda  \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0db8\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dc1\u0db1 \u0d87\u0dbb\u0db9\u0dda",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Investigations begin on the list of goods",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "A senior official of the Department of Archeology told Lankadeepa that the investigations to confirm the items missing from the Presidential Palace have started from today (16).",
        "Last week, Director General of Archeology Professor Anura Manatunga requested the Presidential Secretary to provide the list of items in the Presidential Palace in order to ascertain what items are missing. The list has been handed over to the Department of Archeology accordingly.",
        "Meanwhile, the officer said that the documenting of the damaged goods in the Presidential Palace will continue and that another room in the Presidential Palace was opened yesterday by the Presidential Secretariat officials for inspection purposes.",
        "He said that the investigations are scheduled to be done next week as well.",
        "Meanwhile, the Department of Archeology says that the work of gazetting the Presidential Palace, the Presidential Secretariat, the Temple Palace and the Prime Minister's Office as archaeological monuments has already started."
      ],
